title: Trump picks attorney Brooke Rollins as US agriculture secretary
description: President-elect Donald Trump has selected Brooke Rollins, a longtime ally and former White House aide, to head the Department of Agriculture. Rollins, currently leading the America First Policy Institute, will succeed Tom Vilsack if confirmed by the Republican-controlled Senate. This appointment completes Trump's selection of executive branch department heads. Rollins's background includes agricultural development and experience in Texas politics.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Los Angeles assistant principal arrested for molesting 8 elementary school students
description: David Lane Braff Jr., a 42-year-old assistant principal and counselor, has been arrested on 17 felony counts for allegedly molesting eight elementary school students. The alleged abuse occurred between 2015 and 2019 while Braff worked as a counselor at a Santa Paula elementary school. Prosecutors say Braff molested the students, some as young as six, in his school office.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Islamic State is primed to be thorn in the side of incoming Trump administration
description: The terrorist group has been looking to be active this holiday season, with online chatter about attacks increasingAmid a presidential campaign with foreign policy discussions more focused on the wars in Ukraine, Gaza and Lebanon, the Islamic State stayed under the radar while calling on supporters and operatives to attack Americans on election day.The FBI thwarted a serious plot in Oklahoma City only weeks before the vote, prompting a similar public reaction to news involving the terror group that has become customary of late: is the Islamic State a renewed threat? title: As Band Aid marks 40th anniversary critics take aim at Africa stereotypes
description: Latest version of Do They Know It’s Christmas fundraiser reignites debate about ‘problematic’ lyrics and imagery Forty years ago this week, a group of pop stars gathered at a west London studio to record a single that would raise millions, inspire further starry projects, and ultimately change charity fundraising in the UK.Do They Know It’s Christmas, Bob Geldof and Midge Ure’s festive charity behemoth, would go on to raise almost £150m for famine relief and development in Ethiopia and elsewhere in Africa. To mark the anniversary, on Monday a new version of the single – its fifth – will be released under the name Band Aid 40. Continue reading...
author: Esther Addley
